LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF IDAHO
Sixty-eighth Legislature First Regular Session - 2025
IN THE SENATE
SENATE BILL NO. 1038
BY STATE AFFAIRS COMMITTEE
1 AN ACT
2 RELATING TO HEALTH; AMENDING TITLE 39, IDAHO CODE, BY THE ADDITION OF A NEW
3 CHAPTER 73, TITLE 39, IDAHO CODE, TO PROVIDE THAT THE STATE OF IDAHO
4 SHALL NOT BE COMPELLED TO ENGAGE IN THE ENFORCEMENT OF REQUIREMENTS
5 OR MANDATES ISSUED BY THE WORLD HEALTH ORGANIZATION; AND DECLARING AN
6 EMERGENCY AND PROVIDING AN EFFECTIVE DATE.
7 Be It Enacted by the Legislature of the State of Idaho:
8 SECTION 1. That Title 39, Idaho Code, be, and the same is hereby amended
9 by the addition thereto of a NEW CHAPTER, to be known and designated as Chap-
10 ter 73, Title 39, Idaho Code, and to read as follows:
11 CHAPTER 73
12 MISCELLANEOUS HEALTH PROVISIONS
13 39-7301. WORLD HEALTH ORGANIZATION MANDATES. (1) The state of Idaho
14 and its political subdivisions, including but not limited to counties,
15 cities, towns, precincts, water districts, school districts, school admin-
16 istrative units, or quasi-public entities, shall not be compelled to engage
17 in the enforcement of, or any collaboration with the enforcement of, any
18 requirements or mandates issued by the world health organization.
19 (2) Any requirements or mandates issued by the world health organiza-
20 tion shall not be used in the state as a basis for action or to direct, order,
21 or otherwise impose, contrary to the constitution and laws of this state,
22 any requirements whatsoever, including those for masks, vaccines, or medi-
23 cal testing, or to gather any public or private information about the state's
24 citizens or residents and shall have no force or effect in this state.
25 SECTION 2. An emergency existing therefor, which emergency is hereby
26 declared to exist, this act shall be in full force and effect on and after
27 July 1, 2025.

